overview: The user wanted to improve the overall aesthetic appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic and lacked visual
  sophistication. The agent initiated a comprehensive review of the app's
  styling, including its color palette, typography, layout, and form elements.
  Based on this analysis, the agent decided to implement a new sleep-themed
  design. This involved updating the global CSS with a calming indigo/purple and
  teal color palette, redesigning the main  with subtle
  background elements and a more engaging progress bar, and enhancing the
   with a visually appealing welcome experience. Furthermore,
  individual UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders were
  polished, and section groupings were refined to create a more inviting and
  professional interface. The goal was to transform the app's visual language to
  evoke a sense of calm and trustworthiness, aligning with a sleep assessment
  experience.
